INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("128","1","2010-11-09 16:32:36","2010-11-09 21:32:36","<h2>Freeze 24-7 Anti-Wrinkle Cream</h2>\n<div style=\"float:right\">\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<h5 style=\"background:url(\'http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/h5.gif\'); padding:6px 23px 6px; margin:0px; font-size:1.2em; text-align:center;\">Overall Score: <span style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">9.7</span></h5>\n    <img alt=\"rate\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod6-rate.jpg\" title=\"rate\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"186\" height=\"56\" />\n    <a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"Try It Free\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/try-button.jpg\" title=\"Try It Free\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"142\" height=\"32\" /></a>\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Freeze\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod6-Freeze.jpg\" title=\"Freeze\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"183\" height=\"209\" />\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Average\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod6-average.jpg\" title=\"Average\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"200\" height=\"181\" />\n</div>\n\n<div align=\"center\" style=\"margin-top:20px\"><a href=\"#\">Sign in and<br>\n<img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/write-review.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"write-review\" width=\"143\" height=\"36\" /></a></div>\n\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:425px\">\n  <div class=\"num\">#6</div>\n  <img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/overview-rating.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"overview-rating\" width=\"183\" height=\"18\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-89\" />\n  <p>&nbsp;  </p>\n  Freeze 24-7 originally came onto the spotlight big time after a feature on Oprah. Since then, it has been all over TV and print media.\n\nWhy all the fanfare?\n\n<strong>Clinical Studies:</strong>\n\nIn clinical studies conducted by AMA Laboratories, 100% of respondents experienced a 50-90% reduction in the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles, within minutes of application.\n\nThis is certainly a shocker. We looked into it, and the participants in the studies were women ages 36-79. How many women participated we could not conclusively determine, but it was purportedly a statistically significant sample.\n\n<strong>How does it work?</strong>\n\nFreeze 24-7 works to address a specific cause of fine lines and wrinkles:  the millions of repetitive facial movements we make over time, such as smiling and frowning. These repetitive facial movements cause the facial muscles to constrict in form, as then does the skin.  By relaxing the facial muscles, a reduction in the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles can be achieved.\n\n<strong>Main ingredients:</strong>\n\nGABA – This is the acronym for Gamma Aminobutyric Acid. It is the body’s natural muscle relaxer.\n\nFrom our research, it seems Freeze 24-7 was the first company to use GABA.\n\nBut GABA alone won’t diminish visibility of your fine lines and wrinkles, which is why it is combined with a complex of other supporting ingredients that include:\n\nGynostemma – helps with microcirculation, and assists GABA\n\nEthoxydiglycol – assists Gynostemma\n\n<strong>Other notes:</strong>\n\nIn addition to working on fine lines and wrinkles, Freeze 24-7 may also reduce appearance of stretch marks, enlarged pores, acne scars and rosacea.\n\nYou can see full results within 10 minutes of application, which is quite amazing. At the same time, effects last up to 24 hours, and there is no clinical evidence of a build-up of results with long-term use. Still, this is great as a powerful temporary-fix.\n\nIt does contain eugenol, a fragrance component, which is a skin irritant.\n\nThis is a targeted wrinkle cream and not a moisturizer. You only put it on the spots you need it.  Apply it on clear, dry skin before putting on your moisturizer and foundation. Gently pat and massage it on, and wait one to two minutes until it’s fully absorbed.\n\nDon’t apply too much or you can get flaking.\n\n<strong>Price:</strong>\n \n$125 for 1 ounce\n\n<strong>Shipping:</strong>\n \nStandard shipping and handling is $9.95.\n\n<strong>Money back guarantee:</strong>\n\nThere is no money back guarantee for this product.\n\n<strong>Replenishment program:</strong>\n\nThey have an auto-ship program where you can receive a fresh supply every 60 days.\n\n<strong>Ingredient list:</strong>\n \nWater, Glyceryl Stearate, Sesamum Indicum (Sesame) Seed Oil, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Peg-150 Distearate, Cetyl Alcohol, Cetearyl Alcohol, Gynostemma Pentaphyllum Extract, Aminobutyric Acid, Ethoxydiglycol, Eugenol, Butylene Glycol, Xanthan Gum, Methylparaben, Propylparaben, Ethylparaben, Orchis Maculata Flower Extract, Bismuth Oxychloride\n\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Most helpful Customers’ reviews</h2>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Maryjo B. (Gettysburg, PA)</span></div>\n<p>Love this! I feel my forehead tighten the minute I apply it, and the lines go away. Just make sure to tap it in after putting in on, and wait 2-3 minutes before you put anything else on.</p> \n</div>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Gayle J. (Stillwater, NY)</span></div>\n<p>Compared to all the wrinkle fillers I tried at my drugstore, I got the best results with Freeze 24/7. I only need such a tiny amount that this jar can last very long.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skinca