INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("168","1","2010-11-09 15:35:05","2010-11-09 20:35:05","The original Crème De La Mer was founded by Max Huber, an aerospace physicist, who suffered an accident where he had severe chemical burns. Twelve years later, he completed the formulation of this cream, to help achieve softer, smoother, virtually creaseless looking skin.\n\nCrème De La Mer works to make aging lines and pores less visible.\n\nStars like Jennifer Lopez and Jennifer Aniston have been said to be big fans.\n\n<strong>What makes this cream special?</strong>\n\nThe advertising for this product actually says there is nothing miraculous about the ingredients on their own. What then is supposed to make this cream unique and effective?  The special 3-4 month ‘bio-fermentation process’ the ingredients undergo, and how the ingredients then work synergistically together as a whole.\n\nIn fact, the company even admits: “it’s not entirely clear how Crème de la Mer works”!\n\nThis is in line with what we’ve found, as while there are certainly some good ingredients here, we weren’t overly-impressed by the ingredient list by itself. \n\n<strong>Some of main ingredients:</strong>\n\nThe spotlight ingredient is seaweed extract. This may provide some good benefits to your skin, which include anti-oxidant and ant-inflammatory properties. But as Susan Brawley, professor of plant biology at the university of Maine, points out: “Seaweed extract isn’t a rare, exotic or expensive ingredient.”\n\nOther ingredients include mineral oil and some good vitamins and anti-oxidants.\n\nOnly a small amount of preservatives are needed and placed in this cream, which we like.\n\n<strong>Other notes:</strong>\n\nIf you have very dry skin by the way, this may work well for you.\n\nInterestingly, this cream is also individually hand-filled. We’re can’t be sure if this gives you any extra specific benefits, but it surely feels more prestigious.\n \nHowever, this cream comes in jar packaging. So no matter how effective the seaweed extract and anti-oxidants, they become unstable when exposed.\n\nOne of the drawbacks to this crème is that it contains eucalyptus oil, which can be irritating for all skin types. It also contains Kathon CG, another irritating ingredient that is actually recommended for use only in products that are intended to be rinsed off.\n\n<strong>Price:</strong>\n\n$130 per ounce.\n\n<strong>Money back guarantee:</strong>\n\nWe couldn’t find the length of their return policy on their website, so  we called them to find out.  They told us we can return it at anytime, which is as generous a return policy as it gets!\n\n<strong>Shipping:</strong>\n \nThey offer free shipping on the main website.\n\n<strong>Replenishment program:</strong>\n\nThey have an auto-ship program where you can receive a fresh supply every 30, 45, 60, 75, 90 or 120 days, whichever you decide to set it you. You can cancel or change your replenishments at any time on this program without any penalty.\n\n<strong>Ingredient list:</strong>\n\nSeaweed (Algae) Extract, Mineral Oil (Paraffinum Liquidum), Petrolatum, Glycerin, Isohexadecane, Citrus Aurantifolia (Lime) Extract, Microcrystalline Wax, Lanolin Alcohol, Sesamum Indicum (Sesame) Seed Oil, Eucalyptus Globulus (Eucalyptus) Leaf Oil, Magnesium Sulfate, Sesamum Indicum (Sesame) Seed, Medicago Sativa (Alfalfa) Seed Powder, Helianthus Annuus (Sunflower) Seedcake, Prunus Amygdalus Dulcis (Sweet Almond) Seed Meal, Sodium Gluconate, Potassium Gluconate, Copper Gluconate, Calcium Gluconate, Magnesium Gluconate, Zinc Gluconate, Paraffin, Tocopheryl Succinate, Niacin, Beta-Carotene, Decyl Oleate, Aluminum Distearate, Octyldodecanol, Citric Acid, Cyanocobalamin, Magnesium Stearate, Panthenol, Limonene, Geraniol, Linalool, Hydroxycitronellal, Citronellol, Benzyl Salicylate, Citral, Methylchloroisothiazolinone, Methylisothiazolinone, Alcohol Denat., Fragrance\n\n<strong>Comments:</strong>\n\nSally E. (Baltimore, MD): Very happy with this moisturizer. It keeps my face hydrated. It has beautiful packaging and I love the smell of it!\n\nSusan S. (Lakewood, CO): I decided to purchase this to see what they hype is all about. It seems to share a lot of the same ingredients as nivea, smells like it and feels like it, so I don’t think its worth the money. It was a nice try and it did make my skin feel very soft.\n\nJoyce S. (Boca Raton, FL): I use a lighter cream in the day and added La Mer at night, and I’ve been getting complimented on my skin after using it for a month. Definitely happy with it.\n\nMonty R. (Houston, TX): Didn’t meet my expectations. I thought it would help even my skin tone, calm my skin, and help with my winkles, but it didn’t. My skin did feel moisturized, but for a little while.\n\nShannon W. (Jacksonville, FL): Using it for 3 weeks it works for me. It brightens my skin and I see fewer wrinkles. The most drastic change is even tone. I was hoping it would help with my dark circles but there was no change there.\n\nJessie N. (Oxford, MI): I like La Mer, but a lot of this product goes to waste when I warm it up on my fingers, and it’s not cheap for a one-ounce jar. I’d say get it if you can afford it.\n\nKrisa F. (Santa Clara, CA): At my La Mer counter I got a few samples, have been using this for over a month and I love it. I worried I would break out because I have sensitive skin but I did not. If you have oily skin you should just use less of this product. My skin looks and feels smooth, and my fiancé told me it looks amazing.\n\nZenaida B. (North Baldwin, NY): Buy it! Make sure to get the original formula. It’s not a miracle cream just like nothing is a miracle cream by itself, but it’s a great moisturizer especially if you are over 50 years old. It feels like silk on your skin.\n\nKathleen M. ( Dallas, TX): I have tight, dry and sensitive skin, and this hydrates my skin very well.\n\nGina E. (San Francisco, CA): I did see a reduction in wrinkles, but not as much as I hoped for this price. I will evaluate it for a longer time to see what happens.","Crème De La Mer","","inherit","closed","closed","","121-revision-2","","","2010-11-09 15:35:05","2010-11-09 20:35:05","","121","http://www.skincaresearch.com/168/121-revision-2/","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("138","1","2010-11-09 17:08:11","2010-11-09 22:08:11","<h2>Dr. Murad Intensive Wrinkle Reducer</h2>\n<div style=\"float:right\">\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<h5 style=\"background:url(\'http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/h5.gif\'); padding:6px 23px 6px; margin:0px; font-size:1.2em; text-align:center;\">Overall Score: <span style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">9.7</span></h5>\n    <img alt=\"rate\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod10-rate.jpg\" title=\"rate\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"186\" height=\"56\" />\n    <a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"Try It Free\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/try-button.jpg\" title=\"Try It Free\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"142\" height=\"32\" /></a>\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"DrMurad\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod10-DrMurad.jpg\" title=\"DrMurad\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"183\" height=\"209\" />\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Average\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod10-average.jpg\" title=\"Average\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"200\" height=\"181\" />\n</div>\n\n<div align=\"center\" style=\"margin-top:20px\"><a href=\"#\">Sign in and<br>\n<img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/write-review.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"write-review\" width=\"143\" height=\"36\" /></a></div>\n\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:425px\">\n  <div class=\"num\" style=\"font-family:Arial narrow; font-size:40pt;\">#10</div>\n  <img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/overview-rating.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"overview-rating\" width=\"183\" height=\"18\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-89\" />\n  <p>&nbsp;  </p>\n  Dr. Murad is well known in the skin care industry. He was voted by Vogue as one of the best dermatologists in the country, and is the author of Wrinkle-Free Forever and The Cellulite Solution.\n\nIntensive Wrinkle Reducer originally debuted at the People’s Choice Awards in Los Angeles, and since then has become a hot product.\n\nIt is part of his Age Reform Intensives collection, which is his most advanced treatment collection for reversing the visible signs of aging.\n\n<strong>How it works:</strong>\n\nIntensive Wrinkle Reducer focuses on three factors of aging skin:\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Improving collagen production, as we lose collagen when we age.</li>\n    <li>Increasing nutrients necessary for glycosaminoglycans (which contribute to skin density, volume, and hydration) to flourish in your skin, as they also diminish with age.</li>\n    <li>Provide intense resurfacing of dead skin cells, as dead skin cells do not slough off our skin as frequently when we get older.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<strong>Clinical and independent test studies:</strong>\n\nClinical testing was done at Murad Research Labs, with eleven women between the ages of 40 and 60.   The women had fine lines and wrinkles, dry skin and dull skin tone. Here are the results:\n\nFine lines and wrinkles: Up to a 45% reduction after 8 weeks\n\nSkin firmness: Up to a 40% improvement within 10 minutes of application\n\nSkin hydration: Up to a 37% increase after 8 weeks\n\nSkin tone: Up to a 25% improvement after 8 weeks\n\nWe do think 11 women isn’t a big number for a test, however, its nice to see independent testing was also done on these factors by Barnett Products Corporation, which showed improvements in all these areas as well.\n\nIn their testing, they found a 33% reduction in appearance of fine lines and wrinkles after 4 weeks, and a 55% reduction after 12 weeks. After four weeks, they found a 44% improvement in hydration and a 45% improvement in skin smoothness.\n\n<strong>Key ingredients:</strong>\n\nGlycoNutrient Complex (which consists of Glycosaminoglycans, Glucosamine, marine-derived Polysaccharides, Linoleic Acid and Glycolic Acid)– to smooth appearance of fine lines and wrinkles, and increase the firmness of your skin. It provides intense resurfacing without irritation.\n\nDurian Cell Reform (their proprietary blend of Durian and Glycolic acid)– helps the penetration of GlycoNutrient Complex, and provides anti-oxidant and anti-inflammatory protection.\n\nGlucosamine – for increased production of Hyaluronic acid to help skin keep hydrated.\n\nLipo Amino Acid – helps improve imperfections such as age spots, discoloration and rough texture.\n\n<strong>Other notes:</strong>\n\nWe like that this is not just a quick fix, but the results keep improving with use.\n\nIn addition to fighting against wrinkles, this product works to increase your skin’s radiance, boost hydration levels, improve your skins imperfections and firm and tighten your skin.\n\nIt is good for all skin types.\n\nIn addition to the ingredients mentioned above, it has several great anti-oxidants, water-binding agents, and anti-irritants.\n\nThe one evident downside we see in this great product is that it contains fragrance components that can be irritating to the skin. Cinnamon bark, although having anti-oxidant properties, can also be irritating to the skin.\n\n<strong>Price:</strong>\n \n$150 for 1 ounce\n\n<strong>Shipping:</strong>\n \nFree standard shipping available with purchase.\n\n<strong>Money back guarantee:</strong>\n \nThis product comes with a 100%, 60-day money back guarantee\n\n<strong>Ingredient list:</strong>\n\nIngredients: Water, Glycolic Acid, Glycerin, Propylene Glycol Dicaprylate/Dicaprate, Sodium Hyaluronate, Glucosamine Hcl, Algae Extract, Saccharomyces Cerevisiae Extract, Urea, Macrocystis Pyrifera Extract, Hydrolyzed Wheat Protein, Pvp, Capryloyl Glycine, Sarcosine, Cinnamomum Zeylanicum Bark Extract, Hydroxyethyl Acrylate/Sodium Acryloyldimethyl Taurate Copolymer, Squalane, Polysorbate 60, Rice Amino Acids, Zinc Acetate, Chitosan Ascorbate, Panthenol, Stearyl Alcohol, Cetyl Alcohol, Sclerotium Gum, Stearic Acid, Palmitoyl Hydroxypropyltrimonium Amylopectin/Glycerin Crosspolymer, Lecithin, Vitis Vinifera (Grape) Seed Extract, Magnesium Ascorbyl Phosphate, Tocopherol, Dipotassium Glycyrrhizate, Lysine Lauroyl Methionate, Tocopheryl Acetate, Polydodecanamideaminium Triazadiphenylethenesulfonate, Polyvinyl Alcohol Crosspolymer, Salicylic Acid, Dimethicone, Linoleic Acid, Sodium Hydroxide, Phenoxyethanol, Disodium Edta, Methylparaben, Propylparaben, Citral, Geraniol, Benzyl Benzoate, Citronellol, Hexyl Cinnamal, Limonene, Hydroxyisohexyl 3-Cyclohexene Carboxaldehyde, Fragrance\n\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Most helpful Customers’ reviews</h2>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Cheryl M. (Evansville, WY)</span></div>\n<p>I got this for my mom to try, and I could see a difference around her lips and eyes within two weeks, so I think she will continue using it!</p> \n</div>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Gregory Y. (Baltimore, MD)</span></div>\n<p>It’s not a miracle cream but it works and make my skin look better and smoother.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Nicole C. (Plano, TX)</span></div>\n<p>Very good product by Dr. Murad. I trust him. It works for even my deep wrinkles.</p> \n</div>","Dr. Murad Intensive Wrinkle Reducer","","publish","closed","closed","","dr-murad-intensive-wrinkle-reducer","","","2010-12-20 01:21:04","2010