INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("239","1","2010-11-15 17:17:49","2010-11-15 22:17:49","<h2>Lifecell anti-wrinkle cream</h2>\n<div style=\"float:right\">\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<h5 style=\"background:url(\'http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/h5.gif\'); padding:6px 23px 6px; margin:0px; font-size:1.2em; text-align:center;\">Overall Score: <span style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">9.7</span></h5>\n    <img alt=\"rate\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod1-rate.jpg\" title=\"rate\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"186\" height=\"56\" />\n    <a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"Try It Free\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/try-button.jpg\" title=\"Try It Free\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"142\" height=\"32\" /></a>\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Lifecell\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod1-lifecell.jpg\" title=\"Lifecell\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"183\" height=\"209\" />\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Average\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod1-average.jpg\" title=\"Average\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"200\" height=\"181\" />\n</div>\n\n<div align=\"center\" style=\"margin-top:20px\"><a href=\"#\">Sign in and<br>\n<img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/write-review.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"write-review\" width=\"143\" height=\"36\" /></a></div>\n\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:425px\">\n  <div class=\"num\" style=\"width:74px; padding-left:10px;\">#1</div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/overview-rating.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"overview-rating\" width=\"183\" height=\"18\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-89\" /></p>\n  <p>&nbsp;  </p>\n  <p>\"Does the hype stand up to scientific scrutiny?\n\nThe manufactures of LifeCell claim that it “uses an ingredient, that \"magically tricks\" the eyes...to make wrinkles disappear in the same amount of time it takes to...blink!\n\nWell it\'s not exactly a \"magic trick.\"  It\'s science, which \"appears\" magical.  This \"magic ingredient\" is silicon dioxide in the form of...billions of microscopic three-dimensional crystals!\n\nSo what?\n\nHere\'s \"so what\": Almost nobody knows this...but...the human eye cannot see a wrinkle. What the eye sees is actually the shadow made by the wrinkle. And, since all those billions of microscopic silicon dioxide crystals refract light, when you use this cream... there are no shadows to see.”\n\nDid LifeCell hold up to the rigorous scrutiny of real life testing and give real results?  \n\nWell, I put it to the test. Before applying the cream for the first time, I took a ‘before photo’ of my face. Then, I applied the cream and waited 60 seconds and took an ‘after photo.’ \n\n94 other women who contribute to this review site did the same with their digital cameras.  \n\nFinally, we placed the photos side by side. What you will see is amazing! \n\nWe ALL said, “Where Did My Wrinkles Go?”\n\nThis cream made my fine lines and wrinkles virtually invisible within 60 seconds of application, making me look younger almost instantly.  (The cream is also 100% invisible, odorless and you can’t feel it when you touch your skin).  \n\nPlus, while hiding my fine lines and wrinkles, LifeCell works to reduce their appearance over time and… prevents the appearance of future wrinkles! \n\nIn fact, this convenient all-in-one cream…\nBrightens your skin and makes it glow\nEvens out your skin tone\nMakes your skin smoother \nImproves appearance of photo-damaged skin\nEliminates appearance of fine lines and wrinkles\nProtects your skin from future signs of aging\nDiminishes appearance of age spots\nRevitalizes and re-energizes your skin\nReduces appearance of dark circles and puffiness around your eyes \nImproves your skins firmness and elasticity\nMakes your lips look plumped and provocatively pouty\nRemoves appearance of crow’s feet\n\n\nAnd the best part is the amazing effects of this cream keep building up day-by-day! \n\nListen: I’m probably a bit too jaded and not easy to convince.  So I took another picture with my camera after 40 days of using LifeCell. I now look noticeably younger!  ALL the 94 women who have written back to me look up to 10, 15 even 20 years younger in this short time.  \n\nNegatives: The price was the only negative I can find. It’s one of the more expensive products I’ve found. It was also by far the best.  But then again, price is relative.  When I compare it to Botox or Surgery (which I despise), the price is a steal. \n\nPositives:\nWomen of all colors and skin types keep sending me emails after using it and all have said its worked for them\nThe scientific medical research on their active ingredients is published in independent peer-reviewed medical journals and stands to robust scrutiny.  \nBefore and after photos – including from celebrities and European Royalty\nReal life alternative to botox\nContains Dithiolane-3-Pentanic Acid, Idebenone, Ascorbyl Palmitate (the good kind of vitamin C), Deanol, Acetyl Hexapeptide-3 (alternative to botox)\nTry it free for 30 days (they don’t even charge your card for 30 days)\nOrder by internet, phone, check\n\nGuarantee: The guarantee is the best I’ve ever seen. \nAs you can tell, I can’t recommend LifeCell enough. I’m a tough nut to crack, however, I have to admit that their whole company, South Beach Skincare, from the product to their customer service is the best in the industry.  They have a special promotion going so take advantage of it, before its too late.\n<a href=\"#\"> <br>\n<br>\nTry it for free* and let us know what you think</a>\n\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Most helpful Customers’ reviews</h2>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title