INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("321","2","2010-11-25 11:09:09","2010-11-25 16:09:09","<h2>Perricone MD Cold Plasma Face & Eyes</h2>\n<div style=\"float:right\">\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<h5 style=\"background:url(\'http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/h5.gif\'); padding:6px 23px 6px; margin:0px; font-size:1.2em; text-align:center;\">Overall Score: <span style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">9.7</span></h5>\n    <img alt=\"rate\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod2-rate.jpg\" title=\"rate\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"186\" height=\"56\" />\n    <a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"Try It Free\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/try-button.jpg\" title=\"Try It Free\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"142\" height=\"32\" /></a>\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Lifecell\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod2-lifecell.jpg\" title=\"Lifecell\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"183\" height=\"209\" />\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Average\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod2-average.jpg\" title=\"Average\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"200\" height=\"181\" />\n</div>\n\n<div align=\"center\" style=\"margin-top:20px\"><a href=\"#\">Sign in and<br>\n<img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/write-review.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"write-review\" width=\"143\" height=\"36\" /></a></div>\n\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:425px\">\n  <div class=\"num\">#2</div>\n  <img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/overview-rating.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"overview-rating\" width=\"183\" height=\"18\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-89\" />\n  <p>&nbsp;  </p>\n  <p>Dr. Perricone originally began his walk to fame with his book ‘The Wrinkle Cure.’ He has been in media much lately, and has a whole line of products. His Cold Plasma is one of his best-selling products.  It is advertised as his most comprehensive and efficacious one to date, and it has won a number of awards.</p> \n<p>Marie Claire listed it as one of 25 products that can change your life, and QVC gave it its Q-star award.</p> \n<p><strong>Cold Plasma is formulated to address 10 of the most visible signs of aging:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n    <li>Redness</li>\n    <li>Loss of radiance</li>\n    <li>Discoloration</li>\n    <li>Enlarged pores</li>\n    <li>Uneven skin tone</li>\n    <li>Wrinkles</li>\n    <li>Dryness</li>\n    <li>Loss of firmness</li>\n    <li>Loss of smoothness</li>\n    <li>Impurities</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Overall, it has a good ingredient list. It was developed over five years, with physicists at Los Alamos Laboratories.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Main ingredients include:</strong></p>\n<p>Neuro-peptides – to help with the ten signs of aging</p>\n<p>DMAE – to lift and firm sagging skin</p>\n<p>L-tyrosine – to brighten the skin</p>\n<p>DHA – to hydrate the skin</p>\n<p>However, even though it does contain many good ingredients, the jar packaging exposes them to light and air, which unfortunately makes many of the ingredients unstable once opened.</p>\n<p>Cold Plasma is fragrance-free, which is important in a skin care product. However, for some strange reason, the eye cream contains fragrance chemicals like linalool and farnesol, which can cause irritation and actually reduce collagen production.</p>\n<p><strong>Our research into some questions people often ask:</strong></p>\n<p>What exactly is Cold Plasma? Cold plasma is an ionized gas that has low energy. We have not been able to determine what this has to do with skincare, but it is a unique angle to this product line.</p>\n<p>Cold Plasma also claims to work with an Ionic-Suspension Carrier.  Ions are atoms that have lost or gained electrons, making them positively or negatively charged. While other creams do contain ions that are suspended, we haven’t seen this scientific terminology used with other creams before, and have not been able to conclusively determine whether there is anything different about this or not.</p>\n<p>The only other main issue we could find with Cold Plasma is that it has a fishy smell. If you can tolerate that though, Cold Plasma does seem to work well for many people, of all ages and all skin types. It’s not greasy and it absorbs quickly, and makes a great base for makeup.</p>\n<p><strong>Price:</strong></p>\n<p>The face cream retails at $150 an ounce, and the eye cream retails at $95 for half an ounce.  You can buy them together for $195, a $50 savings.</p>\n<p><strong>Money back guarantee:</strong></p>\n<p>Cold Plasma comes with a 45-day money back guarantee.</p>\n<p><strong>Shipping:</strong></p>\n<p>They offer free shipping on the main website.</p>\n<p><strong>Replenishment program:</strong></p>\n<p>They have an auto-ship program where you can automatically receive a replenishment every 60 days.</p>\n<p><strong>Ingredient list for face cream:</strong></p>\n<p>Water, Glycerin, Tetrahexyldecyl Ascorbate, Phosphatidylcholine, Isopropyl Palmitate, L-Tyrosine, Butylene Glycol, Glyceryl Stearate, Peg-100 Stearate, Cetearyl Alcohol, Oligopeptide-17, Ceteareth-20, Magnesium Aspartate, Zinc Gluconate, Dimethyl Mea (Dmae), Docosahexaenoic Acid, Ascorbyl Palmitate, Phenoxyethanol, Dimethicone, Caprylyl Glycol, Glycolic Acid, Retinyl Palmitate, Saccaromyces Ferment, Elaeis Guineensis (Palm) Oil, Carbomer, Disodium Edta, Tocotrienols, Copper Gluconate, Polysorbate 20, Sorbic Acid, Tocopherol, Sodium Hyaluronate, Acetyl Hexapeptide-8, Palmitoyl Oligopeptide, Astaxanthin, Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-3</p>\n<p><strong>Ingredient list for eye cream:</strong></p>\n<p>Water, Cetearyl Alcohol, Phosphatidylcholine, Isopropyl Palmitate, Glycerin, Tetrahexyldecyl Ascorbate, Glyceryl Stearate, Peg-100 Stearate, Docosahexaenoic Acid, Squalane, Butylene Glycol, Benzyl Alcohol, Ceteareth-20, Magnesium Aspartate, Zinc Gluconate, Olea Europaea (Olive) Fruit Oil, Hydrogenated Vegetable Oil, Disodium Edta, Farnesol, Oligopeptide-17, Elaris Guineensis (Palm) Oil, Carbomer, Copper Gluconate, Tocotrienols, Polysorbate 20, Tocopherol, Sodium Hyaluronate, Fragrance, Linalool, Palmitoyl Oligopeptide, Palmitoyl Tetrapeptide-7</p>\n\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Most helpful Customers’ reviews</h2>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Vicki T. (Wasilla, AK)</span></div>\n<p>I noticed a decrease in my brow furrows very quickly with this.</p> \n</div>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Vicki T. (Wasilla, AK)</span></div>\n<p>I noticed a decrease in my brow furrows very quickly with this.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Eiko R. (Del Ray Beach, FL)</span></div>\n<p>Maecenas tincidunt nisi pulvinar sem ornare id hendrerit arcu vulputate. Sed nisi dolor, sollicitudin eget commodo eget, aliquam in lectus. Nulla consectetur egestas orci vel convallis. Mauris lacus ipsum, pellentesque id consectetur eu, suscipit in augue. Aenean porttitor, tellus at adipiscinl licitudin eget</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Gayle Y. (Newport Beach, CA)</span></div>\n<p>It’s light, goes on great, and soaks in immediately. I use it twice a day right before makeup.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Deborah R. (Aurora, CO)</span></div>\n<p>Great product. I use both the face and eye product together. I began using this because my face felt droopy and I now notice my skin is more elastic. I noticed a difference within a few days, and my friends told me the same. I don’t go a day without it now because I remember what I looked like before I began using this, and I like how I look right now much better. I would recommend this to anyone.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Diane F. (Youngaville, NC)</span></div>\n<p>Expensive but worth the cost.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Grace V. (Grand Prairie, TX)</span></div>\n<p>I noticed my skin more even and glowing in 4 days.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Terry Z. (Seaford, NY)</span></div>\n<p>The product does what it says! My skin is smoother and tighter, very happy with it!</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Stella P. ( Boynton Beach, FL)</span></div>\n<p>I’ve been using it for three weeks and see improvement in my skin color, softness, and radiance.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Dani D. (Seymour, TX)</span></div>\n<p>I use it twice a day as recommended but my jar barely lasts me one month</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Jane S. (San Mateo, CA</span></div>\n<p>I have been suffering from rosacea for over 12 years, my skin red and inflamed, and this helped get it under control, so I highly recommend it.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Frances T. (Rocky Hill, CT)</span></div>\n<p>I hoped this would make a bigger difference, but it didn’t. I don’t know why, the reviews from others tend to seem very good.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Valerie W. (Boulder, CO)</span></div>\n<p>My skin looks so healthy!</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Patricia M. (Jackson, TN)</span></div>\n<p> am happy with this product, I tried other products in this line that I didn’t like but had good results with Cold Plasma. I don’t mind the smell either.</p> \n</div>","Perricone MD Cold Plasma Face & Eyes","","inherit","closed","closed","","118-revision-43","","","2010-11-25 11:09:09","2010-11-25 16:09:09","","118","http://www.skincaresearch.com/321/118-revision-43/","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("323","2","2010-11-25 11:20:29","2010-11-25 16:20:29","<h2>Crème De La Mer</h2>\n<div style=\"float:right\">\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<h5 style=\"background:url(\'http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/h5.gif\'); padding:6px 23px 6px; margin:0px; font-size:1.2em; text-align:center;\">Overall Score: <span style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">9.7</span></h5>\n    <img alt=\"rate\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod3-rate.jpg\" title=\"rate\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"186\" height=\"56\" />\n    <a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"Try It Free\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/try-button.jpg\" title=\"Try It Free\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"142\" height=\"32\" /></a>\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Lifecell\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod3-lifecell.jpg\" title=\"Lifecell\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"183\" height=\"209\" />\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Average\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod3-average.jpg\" title=\"Average\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"200\" height=\"181\" />\n</div>\n\n<div align=\"center\" style=\"margin-top:20px\"><a href=\"#\">Sign in and<br>\n<img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/write-review.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"write-review\" width=\"143\" height=\"36\" /></a></div>\n\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:425px\">\n  <div class=\"num\">#3</div>\n  <img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/overview-rating.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"overview-rating\" width=\"183\" height=\"18\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-89\" />\n  <p>&nbsp;  </p>\n  <p>The original Crème De La Mer was founded by Max Huber, an aerospace physicist, who suffered an accident where he had severe chemical burns. Twelve years later, he completed the formulation of this cream, to help achieve softer, smoother, virtually creaseless looking skin.</p> \n<p>Crème De La Mer works to make aging lines and pores less visible.</p> \n<p>Stars like Jennifer Lopez and Jennifer Aniston have been said to be big fans.</p>\n<strong>What makes this cream special?</strong>\n\nThe advertising for this product actually says there is nothing miraculous about the ingredients on their own. What then is supposed to make this cream unique and effective?  The special 3-4 month ‘bio-fermentation process’ the ingredients undergo, and how the ingredients then work synergistically together as a whole.\n\nIn fact, the company even admits: “it’s not entirely clear how Crème de la Mer works”!\n\nThis is in line with what we’ve found, as while there are certainly some good ingredients here, we weren’t overly-impressed by the ingredient list by itself. \n\n<strong>Some of main ingredients:</strong>\n\nThe spotlight ingredient is seaweed extract. This may provide some good benefits to your skin, which include anti-oxidant and ant-inflammatory properties. But as Susan Brawley, professor of plant biology at the university of Maine, points out: “Seaweed extract isn’t a rare, exotic or expensive ingredient.”\n\nOther ingredients include mineral oil and some good vitamins and anti-oxidants.\n\nOnly a small amount of preservatives are needed and placed in this cream, which we like.\n\n<strong>Other notes:</strong>\n\nIf you have very dry skin by the way, this may work well for you.\n\nInterestingly, this cream is also individually hand-filled. We’re can’t be sure if this gives you any extra specific benefits, but it surely feels more prestigious.\n \nHowever, this cream comes in jar packaging. So no matter how effective the seaweed extract and anti-oxidants, they become unstable when exposed.\n\nOne of the drawbacks to this crème is that it contains eucalyptus oil, which can be irritating for all skin types. It also contains Kathon CG, another irritating ingredient that is actually recommended for use only in products that are intended to be rinsed off.\n\n<strong>Price:</strong>\n\n$130 per ounce.\n\n<strong>Money back guarantee:</strong>\n\nWe couldn’t find the length of their return policy on their website, so  we called them to find out.  They told us we can return it at anytime, which is as generous a return policy as it gets!\n\n<strong>Shipping:</strong>\n \nThey offer free shipping on the main website.\n\n<strong>Replenishment program:</strong>\n\nThey have an auto-ship program where you can receive a fresh supply every 30, 45, 60, 75, 90 or 120 days, whichever you decide to set it you. You can cancel or change your replenishments at any time on this program without any penalty.\n\n<strong>Ingredient list:</strong>\n\nSeaweed (Algae) Extract, Mineral Oil (Paraffinum Liquidum), Petrolatum, Glycerin, Isohexadecane, Citrus Aurantifolia (Lime) Extract, Microcrystalline Wax, Lanolin Alcohol, Sesamum Indicum (Sesame) Seed Oil, Eucalyptus Globulus (Eucalyptus) Leaf Oil, Magnesium Sulfate, Sesamum Indicum (Sesame) Seed, Medicago Sativa (Alfalfa) Seed Powder, Helianthus Annuus (Sunflower) Seedcake, Prunus Amygdalus Dulcis (Sweet Almond) Seed Meal, Sodium Gluconate, Potassium Gluconate, Copper Gluconate, Calcium Gluconate, Magnesium Gluconate, Zinc Gluconate, Paraffin, Tocopheryl Succinate, Niacin, Beta-Carotene, Decyl Oleate, Aluminum Distearate, Octyldodecanol, Citric Acid, Cyanocobalamin, Magnesium Stearate, Panthenol, Limonene, Geraniol, Linalool, Hydroxycitronellal, Citronellol, Benzyl Salicylate, Citral, Methylchloroisothiazolinone, Methylisothiazolinone, Alcohol Denat., Fragrance\n\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Most helpful Customers’ reviews</h2>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Sally E. (Baltimore, MD)</span></div>\n<p>Very happy with this moisturizer. It keeps my face hydrated. It has beautiful packaging and I love the smell of it!</p> \n</div>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Susan S. (Lakewood, CO)</span></div>\n<p>I decided to purchase this to see what they hype is all about. It seems to share a lot of the same ingredients as nivea, smells like it and feels like it, so I don’t think its worth the money. It was a nice try and it did make my skin feel very soft.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Joyce S. (Boca Raton, FL)</span></div>\n<p>I use a lighter cream in the day and added La Mer at night, and I’ve been getting complimented on my skin after using it for a month. Definitely happy with it.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Monty R. (Houston, TX)</span></div>\n<p>Didn’t meet my expectations. I thought it would help even my skin tone, calm my skin, and help with my winkles, but it didn’t. My skin did feel moisturized, but for a little while.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Shannon W. (Jacksonville, FL)</span></div>\n<p>Using it for 3 weeks it works for me. It brightens my skin and I see fewer wrinkles. The most drastic change is even tone. I was hoping it would help with my dark circles but there was no change there.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Jessie N. (Oxford, MI)</span></div>\n<p>I like La Mer, but a lot of this product goes to waste when I warm it up on my fingers, and it’s not cheap for a one-ounce jar. I’d say get it if you can afford it.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Krisa F. (Santa Clara, CA)</span></div>\n<p>At my La Mer counter I got a few samples, have been using this for over a month and I love it. I worried I would break out because I have sensitive skin but I did not. If you have oily skin you should just use less of this product. My skin looks and feels smooth, and my fiancé told me it looks amazing.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Zenaida B. (North Baldwin, NY)</span></div>\n<p>Buy it! Make sure to get the original formula. It’s not a miracle cream just like nothing is a miracle cream by itself, but it’s a great moisturizer especially if you are over 50 years old. It feels like silk on your skin.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Kathleen M. ( Dallas, TX)</span></div>\n<p>I have tight, dry and sensitive skin, and this hydrates my skin very well.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Gina E. (San Francisco, CA)</span></div>\n<p>I did see a reduction in wrinkles, but not as much as I hoped for this price. I will evaluate it for a longer time to see what happens.</p> \n</div>","Crème De La Mer","","inherit","closed","closed","","121-revision-11","","","2010-11-25 11:20:29","2010-11-25 16:20:29","","121","http://www.skincaresearch.com/323/121-revision-11/","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("324","2","2010-11-25 11:19:24","2010-11-25 16:19:24","<h2>La Prairie Cellular Cream Platinum</h2>\n<div style=\"float:right\">\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<h5 style=\"background:url(\'http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/h5.gif\'); padding:6px 23px 6px; margin:0px; font-size:1.2em; text-align:center;\">Overall Score: <span style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">9.7</span></h5>\n    <img alt=\"rate\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod4-rate.jpg\" title=\"rate\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"186\" height=\"56\" />\n    <a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"Try It Free\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/try-button.jpg\" title=\"Try It Free\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"142\" height=\"32\" /></a>\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Lifecell\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod4-lifecell.jpg\" title=\"Lifecell\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"183\" height=\"209\" />\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Average\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod4-average.jpg\" title=\"Average\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"200\" height=\"181\" />\n</div>\n\n<div align=\"center\" style=\"margin-top:20px\"><a href=\"#\">Sign in and<br>\n<img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/write-review.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"write-review\" width=\"143\" height=\"36\" /></a></div>\n\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:425px\">\n  <div class=\"num\">#4</div>\n  <img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/overview-rating.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"overview-rating\" width=\"183\" height=\"18\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-89\" />\n  <p>&nbsp;  </p>\n  La Prairie is well known for using a very uncommon ingredient: Platinum.\n\nYes, we’re talking about the same rare metal as used in jewelry! This is also largely the reason La Prairie comes at the cost of $650 per ounce.\n\nTo be able to be absorbed by your skin, this cream uses a micronized version of platinum called colloidal platinum, which is a suspension of platinum particles in water.\n\nThe big question that everyone asks of course is, what does platinum do in a skin care product?\n\n<strong>How it works:</strong>\n\nJacqueline Hill, a chemist at the Centre de Recherches Biocosmétiques, a Swiss lab, was really the one to come up with the idea use platinum to fight wrinkles. Her explanation for the science behind it was reported in W magazine as follows:\n\n“The skin has an ionic buffer zone that holds in moisture while protecting against free radicals and other damaging force. One side of this zone is made up of positively charged electrons, while the other side is composed of those with a negative charge. When the balance between negative and positive is out of whack due to exposure to pollution, sun damage or stress, the buffer can’t do its job properly, leaving skin both dry and more vulnerable… Platinum re-established a good electrolyte balance, improving moisturization and helping protect the skin.”\n\nWhile this does make sense, it is also the only explanation and evidence we could find, in a lot of research hat we have done, on the effects of platinum on your skin.\n\n<strong>What it does:</strong>\nLa Prairie works to help with fine lines and wrinkles, loss of elasticity and firmness, redness and discoloration, large pores, and uneven texture. It hydrates your skin, helps protect your skins DNA, and the platinum serves to slow down premature aging by maintaining your skins electrical balance.\n\nIt claims to have ‘Exclusive Smart Crystals’ that help guard your skin’s youthful appearance, though we could not confirm the exact combination of ingredients they are referring to by these smart crystals. We can tell you though, for example, that ingredients like mica in their cream can certainly help give your skin a glow.\n\nThey also have blend of ingredients claimed to hydrate the skin by measuring the humidity in the air and providing your skin the adequate amount of moisture it needs.\n\n<strong>Some notes:</strong>\n\nThis cream also contains a number of great anti-oxidants, like Resveratrol and Malachite, as well as a number of good plant extracts and peptides.\n\nHowever, it comes in jar packaging, which can make many of the ingredients unstable.\n\nIt also contains silver oxide, which is a germicide made up of alkaline hydroxide and silver nitrate. Silver nitrate can be bad for your skin.\n\nA nice benefit to consider is you only need to use just a tad of the product on your face, so it can last a long time.\n\nWe think more studies need to be done on the effects of platinum on the skin, but we certainly commend La Prairie on this revolutionary use of platinum in cosmetics, and their cream does work! The only question is, is it worth $650 for an ounce?\n\n<strong>Price:</strong>\n\n$650 for 1 ounce\n\n<strong>Money back guarantee:</strong>\n\nIt comes with a 30-day money back guarantee.\n\n<strong>Shipping:</strong>\n \nFree FedEx Ground shipping. Signature required upon delivery. \n\n<strong>Ingredient list:</strong>\n\nWater, Butylene Glycol, C12-20 Acid Peg-8 Ester, Glycerin, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Squalane, Coco-Caprylate/Caprate, Myristyl Myristate, C12-15 Alkyl Benzoate, Hydroxyethyl Acrylate/Sodium Acryloyldimethyl Taurate Copolymer, Mica, Potassium Cetyl Phosphate, Caprylyl Glycol, Tribehenin, Carbomer, Alcohol, Chondrus Crispus (Carrageenan), Hexylene Glycol, Polysorbate 60, Lecithin, Disodium Edta, Sodium Hydroxide, Glycoproteins, Hesperidin, Glyceryl Acrylate/Acrylic Acid Copolymer, Ceramide 2, Carnosine, Sodium Hyaluronate, Polygonum Cuspidatum Root Extract, Biosaccharide Gum-1, Peg-8, Lactic Acid, Poloxamer 188, Panax Ginseng Root Extract, Tocopherol, Equisetum Arvense (Horsetail) Extract, Hematite Extract, Malachite Extract, Palmitoyl Oligopeptide, Ascorbyl Palmitate, Silybum Marianum Fruit Extract, Citric Acid, Ascorbic Acid, Polysorbate 80, Platinum Powder, Silver Oxide, Fragrance, Benzyl Alcohol, Linalool, Hydroxycitronellal, Alpha-Isomethyl Ionone, Amyl Cinnamal, Hexyl Cinnamal, Evernia Furfuracea (Treemoss) Extract, Geraniol, Benzyl Benzoate, Butylphenyl Methylpropional, Phenoxyethanol, Titanium Dioxide, Iron Oxides\n\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Most helpful Customers’ reviews</h2>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Marguerite H. (Hopsinsville, KY)</span></div>\n<p>I took a big chance with this product. Turned out happy thankfully. My skin looks fabulous. It’s a great moisturizer. I love the texture and the smell. It’s expensive, so I would tell others to try some samples first.</p> \n</div>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Claudette P. (Dallas, TX)</span></div>\n<p>It’s a superb product, and my friends have given me compliments on my skin after using it, but I can’t continue using it because of the price.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Ella C. (Winston Salem, NC)</span></div>\n<p>I tried a sample and it made my skin really silky smooth. My lines became softer. Moisturizes really well. It did feel a bit heavy when I first applied it, but after an hour passed it absorbed well into my skin and my skin felt soft.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Susan L. (Spartanburg, SC)</span></div>\n<p>I think a lot of other La Prairie products are better.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Betty W. (Leesburg, FL)</span></div>\n<p>I just bought my first jar. I pray this works. I want to make sure I am using it properly. Does anyone know how exactly the little spatula that comes with it is supposed to be used? Is it just to scoop the cream out of the jar, or are you supposed to apply the cream to your face with it?</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Admin</span></div>\n<p>It’s to scoop the cream out of the jar, so that you don’t get bacteria into it by dipping your fingers in.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Rory F. (Acworth, GA)</span></div>\n<p>WAY too pricey.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Kim C. (Cape Coral, FL)</span></div>\n<p>My face gets very dehydrated since I live in cold temperature, this moisturizes so good and stays that way most the day.  I like how this makes my skin glow.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Michelle S. (Jamestown, NY)</span></div>\n<p>My mom uses this because of how it tightens and plumps her skin and balances her skin tone and minimizes her wrinkles. I can’t afford it myself, but if you can than it seems to work.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Marcella R. (Cumming, GA)</span></div>\n<p>I don’t think its the platinum by itself, maybe the other ingredients or the mix of everything that makes this effective.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Dee Q. (Boca Raton, FL)</span></div>\n<p>I keep a jar in my fridge with some of my other expensive creams, and it makes me look marvelous, a ‘glitter-like” glow that looks natural. I use it only for special occasions because my husband would kill me if bought another jar haha.</p> \n</div>","La Prairie Cellular Cream Platinum","","inherit","closed","closed","","124-revision-5","","","2010-11-25 11:19:24","2010-11-25 16:19:24","","124","http://www.skincaresearch.com/324/124-revision-5/","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("325","2","2010-11-25 11:22:24","2010-11-25 16:22:24","<h2>StriVectin-HS-Hydro-Thermal Deep Wrinkle Serum</h2>\n<div style=\"float:right\">\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<h5 style=\"background:url(\'http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/h5.gif\'); padding:6px 23px 6px; margin:0px; font-size:1.2em; text-align:center;\">Overall Score: <span style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">9.7</span></h5>\n    <img alt=\"rate\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod5-rate.jpg\" title=\"rate\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"186\" height=\"56\" />\n    <a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"Try It Free\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/try-button.jpg\" title=\"Try It Free\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"142\" height=\"32\" /></a>\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Lifecell\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod5-lifecell.jpg\" title=\"Lifecell\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"183\" height=\"209\" />\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Average\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod5-average.jpg\" title=\"Average\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"200\" height=\"181\" />\n</div>\n\n<div align=\"center\" style=\"margin-top:20px\"><a href=\"#\">Sign in and<br>\n<img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/write-review.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"write-review\" width=\"143\" height=\"36\" /></a></div>\n\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:425px\">\n  <div class=\"num\">#5</div>\n  <img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/overview-rating.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"overview-rating\" width=\"183\" height=\"18\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-89\" />\n  <p>&nbsp;  </p>\n  StriVectin, owned by Klein-Becker, originally came to fame with the famous ‘Better than Botox?’ ads that ran all over the country.\n\n<strong>How it works:</strong>\n\nThis particular product is intended to reduce the appearance of deep lines and wrinkles, as well as enlarged pores and stubborn imperfections.\n\nThe serum works by penetrating what is known as the dermal-epidermal junction of the skin. This is a very critical area in your skin’s architecture.\n\nThere, it is intended to stimulate specialized collagen, ‘decompressing’ the appearance of sharp creases in your skin.\n\n<strong>Spotlight ingredients:</strong>\n\nYeast Extract and Hydrolized soy protein in this serum can help stimulate collagen synthesis.\n\nIt contains sodium polystyene sulfonate, which is a film former, and albumen, which is basically egg white. These two can work together to temporarily tighten your skin.\n\nOther ingredients include Glycerin which improves your skins’ hydration, and Dimethicone is a great emollient that promotes a smooth feel.\n\nIt also has ingredients that help brighten skin tone and relax areas of movement to smooth your skin.\n\nOne thing that jumped out at us is that the ingredient list contains ‘Tripeptide.’ The issue is there is no such ingredient that exists, unless it is followed by a number.\n\n<strong>Other notes:</strong>\n\nOverall, this is a water based-based serum with a few good ingredients, but we  think it can contain more. (Many people combine this with the StriVectin SD cream for a more comprehensive solution).\n\nIt can help reduce visibility of wrinkles, but we have not conclusively determined what it can actually do for other signs of aging.\n\nWe’ve found this serum to be good for different skin types.\n\nUsage of this product is slightly different than with other serums, in that you have to wait 1-3 minutes after putting it on, and then apply a warm and damp facecloth to your face for 30 seconds. The heat of the facecloth is supposed to work in conjunction with the ingredients to activate them deeper into your skin. That’s pretty interesting, and it’s why StriVectin calls this a ‘thermophyillic’ serum.\n\n<strong>Price:</strong>\n \n$153 for 0.9 ounces\n\n<strong>Money back guarantee:</strong>\n\nIt comes with a full 30-day money back guarantee.\n\n<strong>Shipping:</strong>\n \nStandard shipping and handling is $6.50.\n\n<strong>Replenishment program:</strong>\n\nThey have an auto-ship program where you can receive a fresh supply every 45 days, at a discounted rate of $122.40, with free shipping and handling.\n\n<strong>Coupon codes:</strong>\n\nThey do have a coupon code section on their website. We recommend you take a few minutes to Google if any coupons are currently available. Sometimes they even list coupon codes on their own website!\n\n<strong>Ingredient list:</strong>\n\nWater, Tripeptide, Glycerin, Butylene Glycol, Sodium Polystyrene Sulfonate, Yeast Extract (Faex), Peg-8, Albumen, Polypeptide, Hydrolyzed Soy Protein, Glycereth-26, Arginine, Xanthan Gum, Peg-12 Dimethicone, Acrylates/C10-30 Alkyl Acrylate Crosspolymer, Tetrasodium Edta, Phenoxyethanol, Methylparaben, Ethylparaben, Butylparaben, Propylparaben, Isobutylparaben\n\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Most helpful Customers’ reviews</h2>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Jo P. (Conyers, GA)</span></div>\n<p>I use many Strivectin products, and found this to be very effective when you use their whole Deep Wrinkle Remedies Set which includes the wrinkle filler.</p> \n</div>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Kimberly C. (Chicago, IL)</span></div>\n<p>Saw a difference in a few days, and I will never be without this treatment! My laugh lines have diminished by about half. You only have to use a little bit to treat the whole face, which helps with the price of it.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Sheryl T. Scottsdale, AZ)</span></div>\n<p>I am a little upset with this product. I used a whole bottle and had a small decrease in some wrinkles, but the small results didn’t justify the cost.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Allyson H. (Ben Wheeler, TX)</span></div>\n<p>A salesgirl at Sephora gave me a sample, and I have been using it since. The lines on my face are less visible, pores are diminished, and my skin is smoother.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Margaret W. (Johnstown, PA)</span></div>\n<p>Strivectin helped my skin, though the process of using a warm washcloth for 30 seconds after every application was inconvenient.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Ann Marie P. (Mcminnville, TN)</span></div>\n<p>I’ve found this works as a great quick-fix.  Doesn’t do anything at least for me that’s permanent. I use it before going to parties or weddings.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Cristina C. (Surprise, AZ)</span></div>\n<p>Good stuff :) I’m pretty young, have been looking for anti-aging products to keep my skin looking younger as I get older. My skin look soft and beautiful with it, and my skin feels tighter.</p> \n</div>","StriVectin-HS-Hydro-Thermal Deep Wrinkle Serum","","inherit","closed","closed","","126-revision-5","","","2010-11-25 11:22:24","2010-11-25 16:22:24","","126","http://www.skincaresearch.com/325/126-revision-5/","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("326","2","2010-11-25 11:23:43","2010-11-25 16:23:43","<h2>Freeze 24-7 Anti-Wrinkle Cream</h2>\n<div style=\"float:right\">\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<h5 style=\"background:url(\'http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/h5.gif\'); padding:6px 23px 6px; margin:0px; font-size:1.2em; text-align:center;\">Overall Score: <span style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">9.7</span></h5>\n    <img alt=\"rate\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod6-rate.jpg\" title=\"rate\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"186\" height=\"56\" />\n    <a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"Try It Free\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/try-button.jpg\" title=\"Try It Free\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"142\" height=\"32\" /></a>\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Lifecell\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod6-lifecell.jpg\" title=\"Lifecell\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"183\" height=\"209\" />\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Average\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod6-average.jpg\" title=\"Average\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"200\" height=\"181\" />\n</div>\n\n<div align=\"center\" style=\"margin-top:20px\"><a href=\"#\">Sign in and<br>\n<img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/write-review.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"write-review\" width=\"143\" height=\"36\" /></a></div>\n\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:425px\">\n  <div class=\"num\">#6</div>\n  <img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/overview-rating.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"overview-rating\" width=\"183\" height=\"18\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-89\" />\n  <p>&nbsp;  </p>\n  Freeze 24-7 originally came onto the spotlight big time after a feature on Oprah. Since then, it has been all over TV and print media.\n\nWhy all the fanfare?\n\n<strong>Clinical Studies:</strong>\n\nIn clinical studies conducted by AMA Laboratories, 100% of respondents experienced a 50-90% reduction in the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles, within minutes of application.\n\nThis is certainly a shocker. We looked into it, and the participants in the studies were women ages 36-79. How many women participated we could not conclusively determine, but it was purportedly a statistically significant sample.\n\n<strong>How does it work?</strong>\n\nFreeze 24-7 works to address a specific cause of fine lines and wrinkles:  the millions of repetitive facial movements we make over time, such as smiling and frowning. These repetitive facial movements cause the facial muscles to constrict in form, as then does the skin.  By relaxing the facial muscles, a reduction in the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles can be achieved.\n\n<strong>Main ingredients:</strong>\n\nGABA – This is the acronym for Gamma Aminobutyric Acid. It is the body’s natural muscle relaxer.\n\nFrom our research, it seems Freeze 24-7 was the first company to use GABA.\n\nBut GABA alone won’t diminish visibility of your fine lines and wrinkles, which is why it is combined with a complex of other supporting ingredients that include:\n\nGynostemma – helps with microcirculation, and assists GABA\n\nEthoxydiglycol – assists Gynostemma\n\n<strong>Other notes:</strong>\n\nIn addition to working on fine lines and wrinkles, Freeze 24-7 may also reduce appearance of stretch marks, enlarged pores, acne scars and rosacea.\n\nYou can see full results within 10 minutes of application, which is quite amazing. At the same time, effects last up to 24 hours, and there is no clinical evidence of a build-up of results with long-term use. Still, this is great as a powerful temporary-fix.\n\nIt does contain eugenol, a fragrance component, which is a skin irritant.\n\nThis is a targeted wrinkle cream and not a moisturizer. You only put it on the spots you need it.  Apply it on clear, dry skin before putting on your moisturizer and foundation. Gently pat and massage it on, and wait one to two minutes until it’s fully absorbed.\n\nDon’t apply too much or you can get flaking.\n\n<strong>Price:</strong>\n \n$125 for 1 ounce\n\n<strong>Shipping:</strong>\n \nStandard shipping and handling is $9.95.\n\n<strong>Money back guarantee:</strong>\n\nThere is no money back guarantee for this product.\n\n<strong>Replenishment program:</strong>\n\nThey have an auto-ship program where you can receive a fresh supply every 60 days.\n\n<strong>Ingredient list:</strong>\n \nWater, Glyceryl Stearate, Sesamum Indicum (Sesame) Seed Oil, Caprylic/Capric Triglyceride, Peg-150 Distearate, Cetyl Alcohol, Cetearyl Alcohol, Gynostemma Pentaphyllum Extract, Aminobutyric Acid, Ethoxydiglycol, Eugenol, Butylene Glycol, Xanthan Gum, Methylparaben, Propylparaben, Ethylparaben, Orchis Maculata Flower Extract, Bismuth Oxychloride\n\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Most helpful Customers’ reviews</h2>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Maryjo B. (Gettysburg, PA)</span></div>\n<p>Love this! I feel my forehead tighten the minute I apply it, and the lines go away. Just make sure to tap it in after putting in on, and wait 2-3 minutes before you put anything else on.</p> \n</div>\n\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Gayle J. (Stillwater, NY)</span></div>\n<p>Compared to all the wrinkle fillers I tried at my drugstore, I got the best results with Freeze 24/7. I only need such a tiny amount that this jar can last very long.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Maura M. (Foxpoint, WI)</span></div>\n<p>Got best results when using this product alone, with no moisturizer on top. Never tried Freeze’s moisturizer though, maybe that would work better.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Tracy H. (Irvine, CA)</span></div>\n<p>Freeze 24-7 gave me an improvement in the lines I have on my forehead and under at the corner of my eyes. It does what it claims to do.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Cristofer S. (Scottsdale, AZ)</span></div>\n<p>After trying it for a while, it works for the fine lines but not the deeper ones.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Jerry D. (East Moline, IN)</span></div>\n<p>Fantastic product! Been using it for a year now.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Linda W. (Miaaiaaauga, ON)</span></div>\n<p>I used to have big pores on my nose, this definitely helped get rid of them.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Patti L. (Tempe, AZ)</span></div>\n<p>Don’t make the mistake, like someone here, of thinking this is a moisturizer! It is a separate product that freezes your wrinkles.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Linda D. (Riverside, CA)</span></div>\n<p>It tingled on my skin, but I didn’t see any results.</p> \n</div>\n<div id=\"customers-review\">\n<div><img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/5stars.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"5stars\" width=\"126\" height=\"17\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-97\" /> <span>Reggie J. (West Palm Beach, FL)</span></div>\n<p>My wife looks younger when she applies this. Only lasts for a few hours before it wears off.</p> \n</div>","Freeze 24-7 Anti-Wrinkle Cream","","inherit","closed","closed","","128-revision-8","","","2010-11-25 11:23:43","2010-11-25 16:23:43","","128","http://www.skincaresearch.com/326/128-revision-8/","0","revision","","0");
INSERT INTO wp_posts VALUES("327","2","2010-11-25 11:48:42","2010-11-25 16:48:42","<h2>Estee Lauder Perfectionist [CP+] Wrinkle Lifting Serum</h2>\n<div style=\"float:right\">\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<h5 style=\"background:url(\'http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/h5.gif\'); padding:6px 23px 6px; margin:0px; font-size:1.2em; text-align:center;\">Overall Score: <span style=\"font-size:1.4em;\">9.7</span></h5>\n    <img alt=\"rate\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod7-rate.jpg\" title=\"rate\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"186\" height=\"56\" />\n    <a href=\"#\"><img alt=\"Try It Free\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/try-button.jpg\" title=\"Try It Free\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"142\" height=\"32\" /></a>\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; border:#DFEAB0 solid 1px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Lifecell\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod7-lifecell.jpg\" title=\"Lifecell\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"183\" height=\"209\" />\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:202px; margin-bottom:10px;\">\n	<img alt=\"Average\" src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/images/prod7-average.jpg\" title=\"Average\" class=\"aligncenter\" width=\"200\" height=\"181\" />\n</div>\n\n<div align=\"center\" style=\"margin-top:20px\"><a href=\"#\">Sign in and<br>\n<img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/write-review.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"write-review\" width=\"143\" height=\"36\" /></a></div>\n\n</div>\n<div style=\"width:425px\">\n  <div class=\"num\">#7</div>\n  <img src=\"http://www.skincaresearch.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/overview-rating.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"overview-rating\" width=\"183\" height=\"18\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-89\" />\n  <p>&nbsp;  </p>\n  Estee Lauder says this serum is their most effective wrinkle treatment. Upon meticulously comparing it to the rest of the wrinkle products in their line, we agree.\n\n<strong>How it works:</strong>\n\nEstee Lauder created Perfectionist in response to discovering that fine lines and wrinkles on the face look more exaggerated throughout the day.\n\nWhy would this be? Basically, because of all the muscle movement you have all day long. The superficial layer of the skin gets pulled downward and the upper part of your skin folds on top of your wrinkles. This creates an effect of a shadow and making your wrinkles appear deeper. \n\nTo combat this, Perfectionist is infused with polymers to reduce the amplitude of the folding and unfolding of your skin over the course of the day.\n\nIt also contains a blend of peptides, amino acids and proteins that work to increase the collagen production of your skin. Their peptide blend is six times smaller than many other common ones on the market, which allows it to penetrate deep into the skin. Based on in vitro testing they have done, collagen production may begin increasing within just two hours of using this serum. However, they do not make these studies public, so we could not verify these findings.\n\nBecause of all this, Perfectionist claims that its users see as much as a 61% reduction in fine lines and wrinkles after a month of use.\n\nWe’ve found though that this isn’t necessarily the case for deep lines and wrinkles, but more likely for fine lines and wrinkles.\n\n(That’s probably why Estee Lauder has another product, Perfectionist Targeted Deep Wrinkle Filler, which comes in a pen applicator, so you can zero in on those deep frown lines, lip lines, and crow’s feet. It has a lot of great ingredients, and uses Acetyl-Hexapeptide-3 to relax your lines. You can purchase this for an additional $39.50 for 0.5 ounces. The only women we would advise not to use this product is if you use a liquid foundation containing silicones, as combined with this it looks bad).\n\n<strong>Other notes:</strong>\n\nIn addition, upon applying Perfectionist, it fills your wrinkles with what they call a ‘flexible elastomer.’ They claim this allows their customers to see up to a 36% reduction in visibility of the depth, length and number of lines, instantly after use.\n\nIt also contains mineral pigments that can help give your skin a glowing look.\n\nAs a whole, we’ve found this to be a great formula with many beneficial ingredients and antioxidants. It can improve your skins appearance, reduce the appearance of wrinkles, and make your skin look brighter and fresher. We also like the texture of this serum very much.\n\nTwo cons: First, it contains fragrance, which can irritate the skin. Second, it comes in a pump dispenser. Lots of the serum can go to waste by remaining in the bottom of dispensers and not coming out. Pumps can also get stuck every now and then.\n\n<strong>Price:</strong>\n \n$80 for 1.7 ounces.\n\n<strong>Money back guarantee:</strong>\n\nYes, they have a full money back guarantee.\n\n<strong>Shipping:</strong>\n \nThey offer free standard shipping on the main website.\n\n<strong>Gift options:</strong>\n\nThey offer free gift wrapping and a free gift note on a separate card which you can attach.\n\n<strong>Coupon codes:</strong>\n\nThey do have a coupon code section on their website. We recommend you take a few minutes to Google if any coupons are currently available!\n\n<strong>Ingredient list:</strong>\n\nCyclopentasiloxane, Water, Polysilicone-11, Dimethicone, Hdi/Trimethylol Hexyllactone Crosspolymer, Silica, Butylene Glycol, Yeast Extract, Scutellaria Baicalensis Extract, Morus Nigra (Mulberry) Root Extract, Sigesbeckia Orientalis (St. Paul\'s Wort) Extract, Salvia Sclarea (Clary) Extract, Vitis Vinifera (Grape) Fruit Extract, Hordeum Vulgare (Barley) Extract, Chamomilla Recutita (Matricaria) Flower Extract, Triticum Vulgare (Wheat) Germ Extract, Zea Mays (Corn) Kernel Extract, Glycyrrhiza Glabra (Licorice) Root Extract, Narcissus Tazetta Bulb Extract, Boswellia Serrata Extract, Silybum Marianum (Lady\'s Thist